{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":868,"text":"There's something that I'd like you to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4473,"text":"(Video) Reporter: It's a story that's deeply unsettled"},{"time":6957,"text":"millions in China:"},{"time":9011,"text":"footage of a two-year-old girl"},{"time":10891,"text":"hit by a van and left bleeding in the street by passersby,"},{"time":15443,"text":"footage too graphic to be shown."},{"time":18683,"text":"The entire accident is caught on camera."},{"time":21363,"text":"The driver pauses after hitting the child,"},{"time":24171,"text":"his back wheels seen resting on her for over a second."},{"time":28083,"text":"Within two minutes, three people pass two-year-old Wang Yue by."},{"time":32028,"text":"The first walks around the badly injured toddler completely."},{"time":35712,"text":"Others look at her before moving off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41540,"text":"Peter Singer: There were other people"},{"time":42807,"text":"who walked past Wang Yue,"},{"time":45134,"text":"and a second van ran over her legs"},{"time":46853,"text":"before a street cleaner raised the alarm."},{"time":50069,"text":"She was rushed to hospital, but it was too late. She died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55270,"text":"I wonder how many of you, looking at that,"},{"time":59078,"text":"said to yourselves just now, \"I would not have done that."},{"time":62761,"text":"I would have stopped to help.\""},{"time":64965,"text":"Raise your hands if that thought occurred to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68865,"text":"As I thought, that's most of you."},{"time":71741,"text":"And I believe you. I'm sure you're right."},{"time":73708,"text":"But before you give yourself too much credit,"},{"time":76947,"text":"look at this."},{"time":78609,"text":"UNICEF reports that in 2011,"},{"time":82785,"text":"6.9 million children under five"},{"time":86734,"text":"died from preventable, poverty-related diseases."},{"time":92186,"text":"UNICEF thinks that that's good news"},{"time":94448,"text":"because the figure has been steadily coming down"},{"time":97626,"text":"from 12 million in 1990. That is good."},{"time":101679,"text":"But still, 6.9 million"},{"time":104783,"text":"is 19,000 children dying every day."},{"time":110107,"text":"Does it really matter"},{"time":112893,"text":"that we're not walking past them in the street?"},{"time":115798,"text":"Does it really matter that they're far away?"},{"time":121016,"text":"I don't think it does make a morally relevant difference."},{"time":124434,"text":"The fact that they're not right in front of us,"},{"time":126842,"text":"the fact, of course, that they're of a different nationality"},{"time":129003,"text":"or race, none of that seems morally relevant to me."},{"time":132978,"text":"What is really important is,"},{"time":134498,"text":"can we reduce that death toll? Can we save"},{"time":138763,"text":"some of those 19,000 children dying every day?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":143729,"text":"And the answer is, yes we can."},{"time":147347,"text":"Each of us spends money"},{"time":149890,"text":"on things that we do not really need."},{"time":152071,"text":"You can think what your own habit is,"},{"time":154003,"text":"whether it's a new car, a vacation"},{"time":156568,"text":"or just something like buying bottled water"},{"time":159248,"text":"when the water that comes out of the tap"},{"time":161271,"text":"is perfectly safe to drink."},{"time":163801,"text":"You could take the money you're spending"},{"time":165448,"text":"on those unnecessary things"},{"time":167343,"text":"and give it to this organization,"},{"time":169709,"text":"the Against Malaria Foundation,"},{"time":172636,"text":"which would take the money you had given"},{"time":175208,"text":"and use it to buy nets like this one"},{"time":178911,"text":"to protect children like this one,"},{"time":182450,"text":"and we know reliably that if we provide nets,"},{"time":186746,"text":"they're used, and they reduce the number of children"},{"time":190148,"text":"dying from malaria,"},{"time":192604,"text":"just one of the many preventable diseases"},{"time":195412,"text":"that are responsible for some of those 19,000 children"},{"time":199364,"text":"dying every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203012,"text":"Fortunately, more and more people"},{"time":205196,"text":"are understanding this idea,"},{"time":207710,"text":"and the result is a growing movement:"},{"time":211028,"text":"effective altruism."},{"time":213684,"text":"It's important because it combines both the heart and the head."},{"time":218068,"text":"The heart, of course, you felt."},{"time":219779,"text":"You felt the empathy for that child."},{"time":222922,"text":"But it's really important to use the head as well"},{"time":226956,"text":"to make sure that what you do is effective and well-directed,"},{"time":231749,"text":"and not only that, but also I think reason helps us"},{"time":236083,"text":"to understand that other people, wherever they are,"},{"time":239852,"text":"are like us, that they can suffer as we can,"},{"time":243443,"text":"that parents grieve for the deaths of their children,"},{"time":246116,"text":"as we do,"},{"time":247919,"text":"and that just as our lives and our well-being matter to us,"},{"time":252137,"text":"it matters just as much to all of these people."},{"time":255380,"text":"So I think reason is not just some neutral tool"},{"time":258448,"text":"to help you get whatever you want."},{"time":259943,"text":"It does help us to put perspective on our situation."},{"time":264573,"text":"And I think that's why"},{"time":266452,"text":"many of the most significant people in effective altruism"},{"time":271458,"text":"have been people who have had backgrounds"},{"time":273842,"text":"in philosophy or economics or math."},{"time":278580,"text":"And that might seem surprising,"},{"time":280045,"text":"because a lot of people think,"},{"time":281378,"text":"\"Philosophy is remote from the real world;"},{"time":285191,"text":"economics, we're told, just makes us more selfish,"},{"time":289134,"text":"and we know that math is for nerds.\""},{"time":292665,"text":"But in fact it does make a difference,"},{"time":295423,"text":"and in fact there's one particular nerd"},{"time":297359,"text":"who has been a particularly effective altruist"},{"time":301579,"text":"because he got this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303496,"text":"This is the website of the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation,"},{"time":306775,"text":"and if you look at the words on the top right-hand side,"},{"time":310571,"text":"it says, \"All lives have equal value.\""},{"time":314498,"text":"That's the understanding,"},{"time":316367,"text":"the rational understanding of our situation in the world"},{"time":319989,"text":"that has led to these people"},{"time":322250,"text":"being the most effective altruists in history,"},{"time":326931,"text":"Bill and Melinda Gates and Warren Buffett."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329603,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335736,"text":"No one, not Andrew Carnegie, not John D. Rockefeller,"},{"time":339905,"text":"has ever given as much to charity"},{"time":342563,"text":"as each one of these three,"},{"time":345811,"text":"and they have used their intelligence"},{"time":348563,"text":"to make sure that it is highly effective."},{"time":352643,"text":"According to one estimate, the Gates Foundation"},{"time":355731,"text":"has already saved 5.8 million lives"},{"time":359539,"text":"and many millions more, people, getting diseases"},{"time":362697,"text":"that would have made them very sick,"},{"time":364224,"text":"even if eventually they survived."},{"time":367475,"text":"Over the coming years, undoubtably the Gates Foundation"},{"time":370075,"text":"is going to give a lot more,"},{"time":372739,"text":"is going to save a lot more lives."},{"time":376714,"text":"Well, you might say, that's fine if you're a billionaire,"},{"time":380956,"text":"you can have that kind of impact."},{"time":383380,"text":"But if I'm not, what can I do?"},{"time":386328,"text":"So I'm going to look at four questions that people ask"},{"time":389652,"text":"that maybe stand in the way of them giving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393100,"text":"They worry how much of a difference they can make."},{"time":395467,"text":"But you don't have to be a billionaire."},{"time":398692,"text":"This is Toby Ord. He's a research fellow in philosophy"},{"time":402356,"text":"at the University of Oxford."},{"time":404382,"text":"He became an effective altruist when he calculated"},{"time":407970,"text":"that with the money that he was likely to earn"},{"time":410245,"text":"throughout his career, an academic career,"},{"time":412645,"text":"he could give enough to cure 80,000 people of blindness"},{"time":419312,"text":"in developing countries"},{"time":421358,"text":"and still have enough left"},{"time":423631,"text":"for a perfectly adequate standard of living."},{"time":428355,"text":"So Toby founded an organization"},{"time":430352,"text":"called Giving What We Can to spread this information,"},{"time":434438,"text":"to unite people who want to share some of their income,"},{"time":438364,"text":"and to ask people to pledge to give 10 percent"},{"time":441077,"text":"of what they earn over their lifetime"},{"time":443188,"text":"to fighting global poverty."},{"time":446509,"text":"Toby himself does better than that."},{"time":448948,"text":"He's pledged to live on 18,000 pounds a year --"},{"time":453348,"text":"that's less than 30,000 dollars --"},{"time":456092,"text":"and to give the rest to those organizations."},{"time":459492,"text":"And yes, Toby is married and he does have a mortgage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465066,"text":"This is a couple at a later stage of life,"},{"time":468711,"text":"Charlie Bresler and Diana Schott,"},{"time":471707,"text":"who, when they were young, when they met,"},{"time":473234,"text":"were activists against the Vietnam War,"},{"time":476388,"text":"fought for social justice,"},{"time":478367,"text":"and then moved into careers, as most people do,"},{"time":481251,"text":"didn't really do anything very active about those values,"},{"time":484860,"text":"although they didn't abandon them."},{"time":487699,"text":"And then, as they got to the age at which many people"},{"time":490078,"text":"start to think of retirement, they returned to them,"},{"time":493484,"text":"and they've decided to cut back on their spending,"},{"time":496648,"text":"to live modestly, and to give both money and time"},{"time":501793,"text":"to helping to fight global poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506671,"text":"Now, mentioning time might lead you to think,"},{"time":509713,"text":"\"Well, should I abandon my career and put all of my time"},{"time":513337,"text":"into saving some of these 19,000 lives"},{"time":516542,"text":"that are lost every day?\""},{"time":518205,"text":"One person who's thought quite a bit about this issue"},{"time":520907,"text":"of how you can have a career that will have"},{"time":523730,"text":"the biggest impact for good in the world is Will Crouch."},{"time":527451,"text":"He's a graduate student in philosophy,"},{"time":530107,"text":"and he's set up a website called 80,000 Hours,"},{"time":534459,"text":"the number of hours he estimates"},{"time":536133,"text":"most people spend on their career,"},{"time":538505,"text":"to advise people on how to have the best,"},{"time":540717,"text":"most effective career."},{"time":542697,"text":"But you might be surprised to know"},{"time":544911,"text":"that one of the careers that he encourages people to consider,"},{"time":547932,"text":"if they have the right abilities and character,"},{"time":550197,"text":"is to go into banking or finance."},{"time":554864,"text":"Why? Because if you earn a lot of money,"},{"time":558675,"text":"you can give away a lot of money,"},{"time":561014,"text":"and if you're successful in that career,"},{"time":563060,"text":"you could give enough to an aid organization"},{"time":565674,"text":"so that it could employ, let's say, five aid workers"},{"time":570604,"text":"in developing countries, and each one of them"},{"time":573896,"text":"would probably do about as much good"},{"time":575740,"text":"as you would have done."},{"time":577274,"text":"So you can quintuple the impact"},{"time":580284,"text":"by leading that kind of career."},{"time":584405,"text":"Here's one young man who's taken this advice."},{"time":586925,"text":"His name is Matt Weiger."},{"time":588266,"text":"He was a student at Princeton in philosophy and math,"},{"time":592028,"text":"actually won the prize for the best undergraduate philosophy thesis"},{"time":595747,"text":"last year when he graduated."},{"time":598126,"text":"But he's gone into finance in New York."},{"time":601352,"text":"He's already earning enough"},{"time":602957,"text":"so that he's giving a six-figure sum to effective charities"},{"time":607223,"text":"and still leaving himself with enough to live on."},{"time":610952,"text":"Matt has also helped me to set up an organization"},{"time":614823,"text":"that I'm working with that has the name taken"},{"time":617876,"text":"from the title of a book I wrote,"},{"time":619503,"text":"\"The Life You Can Save,\""},{"time":621401,"text":"which is trying to change our culture"},{"time":624142,"text":"so that more people think that"},{"time":627875,"text":"if we're going to live an ethical life,"},{"time":629592,"text":"it's not enough just to follow the thou-shalt-nots"},{"time":633423,"text":"and not cheat, steal, maim, kill,"},{"time":635803,"text":"but that if we have enough, we have to share some of that"},{"time":638690,"text":"with people who have so little."},{"time":642043,"text":"And the organization draws together people"},{"time":644822,"text":"of different generations,"},{"time":646506,"text":"like Holly Morgan, who's an undergraduate,"},{"time":648351,"text":"who's pledged to give 10 percent"},{"time":649868,"text":"of the little amount that she has,"},{"time":651817,"text":"and on the right, Ada Wan,"},{"time":653870,"text":"who has worked directly for the poor, but has now"},{"time":656597,"text":"gone to Yale to do an MBA to have more to give."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661099,"text":"Many people will think, though,"},{"time":662624,"text":"that charities aren't really all that effective."},{"time":666606,"text":"So let's talk about effectiveness."},{"time":668399,"text":"Toby Ord is very concerned about this,"},{"time":670389,"text":"and he's calculated that some charities"},{"time":673276,"text":"are hundreds or even thousands of times"},{"time":676065,"text":"more effective than others,"},{"time":678123,"text":"so it's very important to find the effective ones."},{"time":680959,"text":"Take, for example, providing a guide dog for a blind person."},{"time":685990,"text":"That's a good thing to do, right?"},{"time":688802,"text":"Well, right, it is a good thing to do,"},{"time":690824,"text":"but you have to think what else you could do with the resources."},{"time":693741,"text":"It costs about 40,000 dollars to train a guide dog"},{"time":697985,"text":"and train the recipient so that the guide dog"},{"time":700481,"text":"can be an effective help to a blind person."},{"time":703865,"text":"It costs somewhere between 20 and 50 dollars"},{"time":708137,"text":"to cure a blind person in a developing country"},{"time":711143,"text":"if they have trachoma."},{"time":713153,"text":"So you do the sums, and you get something like that."},{"time":716224,"text":"You could provide one guide dog"},{"time":717970,"text":"for one blind American,"},{"time":720315,"text":"or you could cure between 400"},{"time":723191,"text":"and 2,000 people of blindness."},{"time":726962,"text":"I think it's clear what's the better thing to do."},{"time":730559,"text":"But if you want to look for effective charities,"},{"time":734074,"text":"this is a good website to go to."},{"time":736306,"text":"GiveWell exists to really assess the impact of charities,"},{"time":741190,"text":"not just whether they're well-run,"},{"time":743155,"text":"and it's screened hundreds of charities"},{"time":745455,"text":"and currently is recommending only three,"},{"time":748754,"text":"of which the Against Malaria Foundation is number one."},{"time":752987,"text":"So it's very tough. If you want to look for other recommendations,"},{"time":755610,"text":"thelifeyoucansave.com and Giving What We Can"},{"time":758620,"text":"both have a somewhat broader list,"},{"time":760986,"text":"but you can find effective organizations,"},{"time":764322,"text":"and not just in the area of saving lives from the poor."},{"time":768498,"text":"I'm pleased to say that there is now also a website"},{"time":771074,"text":"looking at effective animal organizations."},{"time":774506,"text":"That's another cause that I've been concerned about"},{"time":776510,"text":"all my life, the immense amount of suffering"},{"time":779114,"text":"that humans inflict"},{"time":780640,"text":"on literally tens of billions of animals every year."},{"time":784897,"text":"So if you want to look for effective organizations"},{"time":787223,"text":"to reduce that suffering,"},{"time":789296,"text":"you can go to Effective Animal Activism."},{"time":792297,"text":"And some effective altruists think it's very important"},{"time":795336,"text":"to make sure that our species survives at all."},{"time":799093,"text":"So they're looking at ways to reduce the risk of extinction."},{"time":802523,"text":"Here's one risk of extinction that we all became aware of"},{"time":805166,"text":"recently, when an asteroid passed close to our planet."},{"time":809323,"text":"Possibly research could help us not only to predict"},{"time":812329,"text":"the path of asteroids that might collide with us,"},{"time":814300,"text":"but actually to deflect them."},{"time":817092,"text":"So some people think that would be a good thing to give to."},{"time":819756,"text":"There's many possibilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821998,"text":"My final question is,"},{"time":823709,"text":"some people will think it's a burden to give."},{"time":826740,"text":"I don't really believe it is."},{"time":828373,"text":"I've enjoyed giving all of my life"},{"time":830553,"text":"since I was a graduate student."},{"time":831871,"text":"It's been something fulfilling to me."},{"time":834704,"text":"Charlie Bresler said to me that he's not an altruist."},{"time":837135,"text":"He thinks that the life he's saving is his own."},{"time":840509,"text":"And Holly Morgan told me that she used to battle depression"},{"time":844436,"text":"until she got involved with effective altruism,"},{"time":846668,"text":"and now is one of the happiest people she knows."},{"time":850214,"text":"I think one of the reasons for this"},{"time":851987,"text":"is that being an effective altruist helps to overcome"},{"time":855254,"text":"what I call the Sisyphus problem."},{"time":858125,"text":"Here's Sisyphus as portrayed by Titian,"},{"time":861318,"text":"condemned by the gods to push a huge boulder"},{"time":864341,"text":"up to the top of the hill."},{"time":866020,"text":"Just as he gets there, the effort becomes too much,"},{"time":869070,"text":"the boulder escapes, rolls all the way down the hill,"},{"time":872311,"text":"he has to trudge back down to push it up again,"},{"time":875615,"text":"and the same thing happens again and again"},{"time":878034,"text":"for all eternity."},{"time":880416,"text":"Does that remind you of a consumer lifestyle,"},{"time":883431,"text":"where you work hard to get money,"},{"time":886113,"text":"you spend that money on consumer goods"},{"time":888358,"text":"which you hope you'll enjoy using?"},{"time":891930,"text":"But then the money's gone, you have to work hard"},{"time":894661,"text":"to get more, spend more, and to maintain"},{"time":897561,"text":"the same level of happiness, it's kind of a hedonic treadmill."},{"time":900568,"text":"You never get off, and you never really feel satisfied."},{"time":903934,"text":"Becoming an effective altruist gives you"},{"time":906926,"text":"that meaning and fulfillment."},{"time":908416,"text":"It enables you to have a solid basis for self-esteem"},{"time":912607,"text":"on which you can feel your life was really worth living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916732,"text":"I'm going to conclude by telling you"},{"time":919288,"text":"about an email that I received"},{"time":921421,"text":"while I was writing this talk just a month or so ago."},{"time":926345,"text":"It's from a man named Chris Croy, who I'd never heard of."},{"time":929372,"text":"This is a picture of him showing him recovering from surgery."},{"time":933791,"text":"Why was he recovering from surgery?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":936325,"text":"The email began, \"Last Tuesday,"},{"time":939882,"text":"I anonymously donated my right kidney to a stranger."},{"time":943740,"text":"That started a kidney chain"},{"time":945825,"text":"which enabled four people to receive kidneys.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":950494,"text":"There's about 100 people each year in the U.S."},{"time":952933,"text":"and more in other countries who do that."},{"time":955651,"text":"I was pleased to read it. Chris went on to say"},{"time":957815,"text":"that he'd been influenced by my writings in what he did."},{"time":961187,"text":"Well, I have to admit, I'm also somewhat embarrassed by that,"},{"time":964610,"text":"because I still have two kidneys."},{"time":970872,"text":"But Chris went on to say that he didn't think"},{"time":973138,"text":"that what he'd done was all that amazing,"},{"time":975818,"text":"because he calculated that the number of life-years"},{"time":979325,"text":"that he had added to people, the extension of life,"},{"time":981873,"text":"was about the same that you could achieve"},{"time":984682,"text":"if you gave 5,000 dollars to the Against Malaria Foundation."},{"time":990518,"text":"And that did make me feel a little bit better,"},{"time":994594,"text":"because I have given more than 5,000 dollars"},{"time":998148,"text":"to the Against Malaria Foundation"},{"time":1000995,"text":"and to various other effective charities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005898,"text":"So if you're feeling bad"},{"time":1007332,"text":"because you still have two kidneys as well,"},{"time":1011414,"text":"there's a way for you to get off the hook."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014048,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1015248,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}